## 5. Platoon Assignment (per Papa's standing rule)

| Step | Model | Cost | Speed | Why |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| P0 keep_alive + timeout | n/a (Python) | $0 | <1ms | Pure config change |
| P1.a temp/N change | n/a (Python) | $0 | <1ms | One-line edits in `judge.py` |
| P1.b prompt anonymization | n/a (prompt-string) | $0 | n/a | Edit `autowiki/prompts/judge_v1.md` |
| P1.c rubric redefinition | n/a (prompt-string) | $0 | n/a | Same file |
| P1.d per-section sub-rubric | **Rakon** (deepseek-r1:14b, judge) | $0 | +30-60s per tick | Same model, 10× the calls (one per section) |
| P2 anchor paper lookup | n/a (ADS + Kun) | $0 | 30 min | Manual or thin script |
| P2 propose_claim_insert subtopic | **AstroSage** (70B local) | $0 | ~60s/claim | Existing proposer path |
| P3 arXiv backfill | n/a (Python + ADS) | $0 | ~10 min | DB query + classifier loop |
| P4 round-robin section | n/a (Python) | $0 | <1ms | Track last-rewritten section in DB column |

No new model spend. P1.d is the only LLM-bearing change, and it's the same Rakon judge model just called 10× per tick (one rubric per section instead of one whole-page rubric). Total: ~10 minutes of extra judge time per tick, which at 15-min tick interval still leaves plenty of headroom.

---

## 6. Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Post-P0: autowiki_tick commits at least 3 of the next 5 beat-scheduled ticks (vs. 0/6 in the 19:49-20:04 KST window)
- [ ] Post-P1.a: 5 parallel judge calls produce ≥2 distinct rubric outputs (vs. byte-identical today)
- [ ] Post-P1.c: at least one autowiki_runs row has u1_median ≥ 9.5 (vs. ceiling 9.09 today)
- [ ] Post-P2: `compute_health_score(page).components.depth ≥ 0.9` (vs. 0.7 today)
- [ ] Post-P3: `freshness ≥ 0.85` and 2024+ evidence count ≥ 100 (vs. 73 today)
- [ ] Post-P4: every section has been rewritten at least once in the last 7 days
- [ ] Cumulative: galaxy-evolution autowiki_runs.q1 reaches 0.95+ on at least 3 consecutive commits

---

## 7. Open questions for Papa

1. **Rakon 671B vs 32B (still pending).** Doesn't affect this roadmap directly — the autowiki judge uses deepseek-r1:14b, not the Rakon 671B. But `rakon_deep_pass` (the deeper synthesis task) and any future "deep reasoning" steps depend on Papa's call. If we keep 671B, the `deep_synthesis._call_rakon` keep_alive fix becomes urgent (separate from this doc).
2. **Should we raise the debate-claim target from 4 to 8?** (P5 above) Higher target = `claim_insert_debate` keeps firing, which improves `open_questions_q` rubric. But it also requires the proposer to find 4 *new* genuine debates that don't already have claims — galaxy-evolution may not have 8 active debates that meet the bar.
3. **For P1.d (per-section sub-rubric), do we keep a separate "page-level" rubric for backwards-compat with `autowiki_runs.u1_median`, or replace it entirely?** My recommendation: keep both. The page-level number is the historical metric; the sub-rubric is the diagnostic.
4. **Pilot expansion timing.** Once galaxy-evolution hits 0.95, what's the next pilot page? Black-hole-mergers and exoplanets both have low health_score and would benefit from the same loop.

— 🔬 Kun, 2026-05-12 21:00 KST

